<db:para>Qt Designer{Qt Designer} is an excellent tool to preview style sheets. You can right-click on any widget in Designer and select <db:guilabel>Change styleSheet...</db:guilabel> to set the style sheet.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/designer-stylesheet-options.png"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
<db:para>In Qt 4.2 and later, Qt Designer also includes a style sheet syntax highlighter and validator. The validator indicates if the syntax is valid or invalid, at the bottom left of the <db:guilabel>Edit Style Sheet</db:guilabel> dialog.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/designer-validator-highlighter.png"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
<db:para>When you click <db:guilabel>OK</db:guilabel> or <db:guilabel>Apply</db:guilabel>, Qt Designer will automatically display the widget with its new stylesheet.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/designer-stylesheet-usage.png"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
